  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I completely delete all Adobe CS6 files on my Mac?",
  "response": "To completely delete all Adobe CS6 files from your Mac, you need to follow a series of steps to ensure all related files and folders are removed. Here's a comprehensive guide:\n\n1. **Uninstall Adobe CS6 Applications:**\n   - Open Finder and navigate to the Applications folder.\n   - Locate the Adobe CS6 folder.\n   - In the Adobe CS6 folder, find and run the \"Uninstall Adobe [Application]\" for each CS6 application you have installed (such as Photoshop, Illustrator, etc.).\n\n2. **Remove Adobe CS6 Preferences and Support Files:**\n   - Open Finder and go to your home directory (usually named with your username).\n   - Navigate to `Library` (if you don't see it, hold the `Option` key and click on the `Go` menu in Finder, then select `Library`).\n   - In the `Library` folder, look for and delete the following folders and files:\n     - `Application Support/Adobe`\n     - `Preferences/com.adobe.*` (any files starting with `com.adobe`)\n     - `Caches/com.adobe.*` (any files starting with `com.adobe`)\n     - `Logs/Adobe`\n     - `Saved Application State/com.adobe.*` (any files starting with `com.adobe`)\n     - `LaunchAgents/com.adobe.*` (any files starting with `com.adobe`)\n\n3. **Remove Adobe CS6 System Files:**\n   - Open Finder and navigate to `Macintosh HD` > `Library`.\n   - Delete the following folders and files (if present):\n     - `Application Support/Adobe`\n     - `Preferences/com.adobe.*` (any files starting with `com.adobe`)\n     - `Caches/com.adobe.*` (any files starting with `com.adobe`)\n     - `LaunchDaemons/com.adobe.*` (any files starting with `com.adobe`)\n     - `Logs/Adobe`\n\n4. **Remove Adobe CS6 Fonts:**\n   - Open Finder and navigate to your home directory.\n   - Go to `Library` > `Fonts`.\n   - Look for and delete any fonts installed by Adobe CS6.\n\n5. **Remove Adobe CS6 Plugins:**\n   - Open Finder and navigate to your home directory.\n   - Go to `Library` > `Application Support`.\n   - Look for and delete any plugins related to Adobe CS6.\n\n6. **Check for Other Adobe Files:**\n   - Use Finder\u2019s search functionality to look for any remaining Adobe-related files:\n     - Type `Adobe` in the search bar and ensure you are searching \"This Mac.\"\n     - Review the search results and delete any remaining files and folders related to Adobe CS6.\n\n7. **Empty Trash:**\n   - After you've deleted all the files and folders, make sure to empty your Trash to permanently remove them.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to completely remove all Adobe CS6 files from your Mac. If you encounter any difficulties or need further assistance, you can refer to Adobe's official support resources or use dedicated uninstaller software designed for removing Adobe products.",
